      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GO EASY ON ME (9) placed from this barrier when fresh then got the job done in impressive style last start. coming from a wide barrier to spank her rivals by 36 metres at Bathurst. Could go through her grades now. IM DOWNBYTHEBEACH NZ (7) is a newcomer to the Julie Douglas yard from NZ where he raced just once, coming from a wider barrier to score at Motukarara. Has plenty of upside and could make an immediate impact on this side of the Tasman. LAMBRO MACH (11) has continued his good form by placing in both starts off a let-up. Fitter for those hitouts and owns good statistics at the circuit and the distance. RONNIE THE HAMMER (13) draws wide on the back row but has sound form including a Kilmore win two back and he usually races well here.",
